HEADWORD: Strathspey
<hw>Strath"spey`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from
the district of <ets>Strath Spey</ets> in Scotland.]</ety> <def>A lively
Scottish dance, resembling the reel, but slower; also, the
tune.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

